  "text": "Note however that search slopes were overall quite high and far from efficient even in the relevant conditions (i.e. around 40 ms/item), especially when compared to the equivalent conditions in [CITATION_1]  typically between 10 and 20 ms/item). In this sense it is difficult to argue for strong bottom-up attentional capture by static objects.",
